header.gameNote: DR PEPPER CLASSIC AT CHATTANOOGA TN

article.headline: Belmont 84, Murray St. 67
article.story: CHATTANOOGA, Tenn. (AP) -- Justin Hare scored 19 points to lead Belmont in an 84-67 win over Murray State in the consolation game of the Dr Pepper Holiday Classic Sunday night. Belmont (8-6) jumped out to a 27-3 lead at 10:40 in the first half and never trailed. The Bruins forced 20 turnovers, scoring 32 points off of them and had 12 steals while Murray State (5-6) forced only eight turnovers, for only 9 points. Despite fairly even shooting, with Belmont at 50 percent for the game and Murray State at 52 percent, the Bruins dominated from beyond the arc, connecting on 14 of 32 while Murray State hit only 4 of 13. Also helping Belmont were Matthew Dotson with 17 points and Shane Dansby 16 points. Bruce Carter led Murray State with 18 points and Tony Easley added 11.
